JOHANNESBURG – South Africa’s net foreign reserves rose to $44.226 billion in August from $43.906 billion in July, the Reserve Bank said on Friday. Gross reserves increased to $49.948 billion at the end of August from $49.360 billion the previous month, central bank data showed. The forward position representing the central bank’s unsettled, or swap, transactions fell to $231 million in August from $539 million in July. (Reuters)